         What do they need to give us in PooP (imo)?</P><P> - 2 new pets (62, 65), both warriors (or SKs if they are so inclined, just don't screw em up).  A pet at 61 is way too close to EoT (getting through 60 is a breeze.)  The new pet buff seems alright, add a small damage shield to it (ala Banshee Aura).</P><P> - New shield spells seem nice, upgrade the mana regen on the new rune to 2 or 3.</P><P> - New undead-only mez and charm could be very nice depending on what the zones there look like.  Remember, they are useless unless 90+% of the mobs in an area are undead.  If there is a plane full of undead (and summoned), I can see necros being very useful.</P><P> - Vexing upgrade needs to be improved to 1440 heal at least.</P><P> - Touch of Night ugprade at 64 (1200?)</P><P> - Deflux upgrade at 61 (666 dmg :))</P><P> - And the big one, new DoTs.  The new poison and disease ones are nice since our disease and poison lines ended prematurely, but they better not stop there.  An upgrade to Funeral Pyre at 65, an upgrade to splurt at 63, and a cold based DoT line at 61 and 64 (medium mana cost, medium-high damage, no initial DD).  Keep the balance between shamans, druids and necros in check.  Shamans should NOT be better dotters regardless of how much they whine about it.</P><P> - Fetter!  Thats the only root spell (non-druid) we don't get, mainly because our root line started late at 34.  62/63/64 or so.<BR> <BR> - Upgraded fear and screaming terror.  Fear kiting should still be a semi-viable tactic, and with mobs at 55+ its not (immune to fear).  And we should still be able to ghetto mez.</P><P> - Upgrade to Corpral Empathy (instant heal) and Shadowbond would be nice.</P><P><BR>Daedrea Darksoul<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
